# ARKHOS Architecture Changelog

### EK validators 27/38 → 28/38 — Wave 9b upper_corner_required v1 (2026-05-04)

**One new validator unblocking the Wave 7 deferred case (BG1 lower → upper covering inner corner zone).**

**Commit `2036a90`.** Rule implemented:

1. **`upper_corner_required`** — anchor-proximity check, NOT a strict TG1 requirement. Per user clarification (Wave 7): BG1 lower does NOT mandate TG1 upper — it is one of three valid configurations (TG1 corner upper / single-arm uppers extending past corner / pencil-at-corner terminating uppers / no uppers at all). v1 implements the weakest check that still catches the gross "lower corner with no upper coverage in the inner corner zone" anti-pattern: for each `:l_corner_lower` (BG1), compute anchor `xy = (bbox_max_x, bbox_max_y)` (NE-orientation bias), and require ANY `:upper_cabinet` OR `:l_corner_upper` with center within 200mm of that anchor. Vacuous when 0 corners or 0 uppers present. Verified on Villu: BG1 corner_max=(3339, 0); TB1#3 at X=2869..3339 Y=-367..-21 has center within 200mm of anchor → covered → ok. Negative test via snapshot mutation removing all uppers within 200mm of anchor → fires correctly with the "add TG1 or extend a row upper" message.

**Anchor heuristic (v1 limitation):** `bbox_max` works for NE-corner L-kitchens (Villu reference). For NW/SW/SE orientations the anchor would land on the wrong corner of the BG1 bbox. v2 needs orientation detection (read corner FACADE def-local axis OR cluster-row geometry around BG1) before generalizing to all four L-orientations. U-shape with 2× BG1 also untested. Acceptable v1 because Villu is the active reference and the rule is intentionally a soft "anti-pattern" check, not a strict requirement.

**Live audit Villu after Wave 9b:** 28/28 validators ok=true, 0 violations, 0 orphans. Positive-tested on Villu (1 corner, 9 uppers, anchor covered by TB1#3); negative-tested via snapshot mutation (uppers count drops to 9 - covered → fires with single violation message).

