### EK validators 24/38 → 27/38 — Wave 9 (2026-05-04)

**Three new validators bringing live coverage from 24 to 27 of 38 manifest rules (71%).**

**Commit (pending).** New rules implemented:

1. **`wall_end_filler_applies_to_uppers_and_mezzanine`** — v1 covers W-wall side of upper rows ONLY. For each Y-center band cluster of uppers (300mm bins), the leftmost upper is the W endpoint of that row. If its X_min is within 30mm of the inferred W wall, a PANEL-FACADE ComponentInstance must be within 50mm proximity on the W side with Y+Z overlap. Verified on Villu: TB1#4 at X=19 has PANEL-FACADE#6 at X=-0.3..19 abutting at 0mm gap → passes.

2. **`backsplash_work_zone`** (warning) — backsplash X-extent must lie within work zone (sink+cooktop+work cabinets) X-span ± 600mm tolerance. Vacuous on Villu (no backsplash); negative-tested via snapshot mutation injecting a backsplash with X-span -2000..8000 → flagged.

3. **`cutout_markers_exempt_from_custom_geometry_ban`** (warning) — Sketchup::Group with name matching `/\Acutout[_-](sink|cooktop|hob|other)/i` must carry the `studiokook_cutout` AD. Vacuous on Villu (0 top-level groups); negative-tested via snapshot mutation injecting a group named `cutout_sink_main` without AD → flagged.

**Back-wall vs end-wall disambiguation (new lesson):** First-pass `wall_end_filler` v1 checked any upper within 30mm of wall axes (W/E) and fired 5 false positives on Villu E-arm uppers — all had X_max=3339=E_wall, but that is the BACK wall of the E-arm row (which runs along the Y-axis), not the row endpoint. The row endpoints are at Y_min/Y_max, not X_max. Without row-axis cluster detection (uppers clustered by Y → row along X; clustered by X → row along Y), a strict X-side wall check confuses back-wall adjacency (covered by `wall_adjacency`) with row termination (this rule). Fixed in same session by restricting v1 to W-wall side only and clustering uppers by Y band before picking the leftmost. E/N/S walls + lower rows + mezzanine extension deferred to v2 with proper row-axis inference.

**Live audit Villu after Wave 9:** 27/27 validators ok=true, 0 violations, 0 orphans. All three new validators positive-tested where applicable on Villu (wall_end_filler) or vacuously passed (backsplash_work_zone, cutout_markers_exempt) and negative-tested via snapshot mutation.

