### EK validators 16/38 → 17/38 — eurocut_joint_width_canon (2026-05-04)

**Commit `a0f52f5`.** Library `TT_STRAIGHT` ships with eurocut joint width = **30mm DEFAULT**. Studiokook canonical = **10mm**. The right-side width is FORMULA-DRIVEN from the left (`_l0_component_512_eurocut_right_width_formula = "l0_component_502_eurocut_left_width"`), so the source-of-truth key is `l0_component_502_eurocut_left_width`. Setting the right key directly is overwritten on `dc.redraw`.

Snapshot extension: `:eurocut_width_mm` on countertop entries (reads instance AD with def-AD fallback). Validator fires only on primary CTs that have an active joint mode (`eurocut_left` or `eurocut_right` ∈ {`"2"` papa, `"3"` mama}) but width != 10mm ±0.5mm.

Apply 10mm canon after fresh placement:
```ruby
dc.set_attribute(ct_inst, 'l0_component_502_eurocut_left_width', 0.3937007874015748)
dc.redraw(ct_inst)
```

Verified on Villu rebuild — both CTs at 10mm pass; negative test (snapshot mutation to 30mm) fires expected violation.

